courses.learning_outcomes:
At the end of the course of studies / Upon successful completion of this course, students should be able to:

1. Understand and implement state-of-the-art robotics and embodied-AI methodologies within advanced robotic systems such as humanoids;

2. Deploy sophisticated robotic platforms to tackle complex, practical problems including competitive robotics events and real-world application scenarios;

3. Demonstrate competencies in system integration, advanced programming, problem-solving under constraints, and collaborative teamwork;

4. Apply practical knowledge drawn from research papers and industrial best practices to real-world robotic challenges;

5. Execute rapid prototyping, performance optimization, and strategic planning in robotics projects; and

6. Deliver robust solutions in time-critical environments through competition-based projects and practical applications.

At the end of the course of studies, a student should be able to

1. Have a good understanding and appreciate the characteristics of a robotics work environment, including employer expectation, management structure of a team, industrial standards and practices, trends and common issues in robotics, etc.;
2. Carry out basic duties in a robotics work environment;
3. Exhibit good etiquette in the workplace;
4. Work independently as well as in a team environment; and
5. Communicate effectively and efficiently with peers, supervisors and possibly also clients.
